[1] Sri Lanka
Date: 27 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Daily News, Sri Lanka, 28 May 2004 [edited]
<http://www.dailynews.lk/2004/05/28/new20.html>


Dengue claims 16 lives
-----------------------
The dengue epidemic has claimed 16 lives so far this year [2004], while the
number of suspected cases had risen to 3137 as of yesterday.

The highest number of cases have been reported from Gampaha (638) followed
by Colombo [the capital] with 632 cases and Kandy (542). Kurunegala and
Trincomalee have also recorded a high prevalence of dengue. Officials
warned that there was an increase in the number of dengue cases patients in
May [2004] compared to the previous month. "The number of cases reported
last month was 512. It was 533 cases this month." (BM)

--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

