[2] Venezuela
Date: Tue, 25 May 2004 16:05:48 -0400
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: El Universal, Venezuela 25 May 2004 [in Spanish, summarized by
Mod.JW; edited]
<http://www.eluniversal.com/2004/05/25/25278E.shtml>


Jose Mendoza, director of Epidemiology, stated that [epidemiological] week
19 ended with 509 cases [compared with 677 cases during epidemiological
week 12 and 579 cases during epidemiological week 13; see ref. (12) below.
- Mod.JW]. States most affected that week were Falcon with 62 cases,
Trujillo with 55, the Capital District with 53, Merida with 52, Zulia y
Miranda with 40 each, and Nueva Esparta with 39.

